BANANA CAKE

2 1/2 c all-purpose flour	1/2 c shortening
1 1/2 c sugar			1 c mashed ripe banana
1 1/2 tsp baking powder		2/3 c buttermilk or sour milk
1 tsp baking soda		2 eggs
1 tsp salt			1 tsp vanilla

Grease and lightly flour 2 9-inch round cake pans.  In a mixer bowl
combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.  Add
shortening and banana; beat at low speed until combined.  Add
buttermilk or sour milk, eggs, and vanilla.  Beat 2 minutes at medium
speed.  Turn batter into pans.  Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until
cake tests done.  Cool 10 minutes in pans.  Remove from pans and cool
on wire racks.
